AGI - A mass of air of marine polar origin, descending from the Celtic Sea, will bring a decrease of temperatures even 10 C towards the Centre-South, after reaching the north with snowfall up to 800 meters on the border Alps. Lorenzo Tedici, meteorologist at www.iLMeteo.it, confirms the power of this 'cold' break in the heart of April, but indicates that it is only a pseudo-invernal illusion. From Thursday will return the North African sun and heat everywhere. In the coming hours still strong storms in the North, locally at the Center between Sardinia, Tuscany, Umbria, Marche and Lazio; the most intense phenomena are expected on the Po Valley, especially between Lombardy and Emilia, even with possible hailed premises. At the Centre the phenomena will be more isolated, while in the South we can have some reverse premises between Campania and Sicily.
&nbsp;
The wind will also be the protagonist: it will blow strong on the Liguria of Ponente, in Sardinia and towards the Basso Tirreno. 'The snow will fall again on the Alps until the afternoon evening with snow in the skis around 1700-1800 meters. From Thursday, instead, everything will change again with an increase of maximum temperatures of about 6-7 C on the Tyrrhenian belt and 12-14 C on the Alps: from the pseudo-winter we will pass to a almost summer with peaks of 30 C, previewed once again in the next weekend also to the North. Weather swing: down of 10 C and then up of 10 C in 24-36 hours. The thermal collapse will be canceled by Friday from the sudden and subtaneous increase caused by the remonta of the North African anticyclone. Then from Friday we get warm again.
&nbsp;
In detail tomorrow > to the north: very unstable on North West, Emilia and Western Veneto. In the center: a few reverses on Tuscany, Umbria, Marche, Lazio and Sardinia. To the south: irregular clouds, some rain on Campania and Sicily.
&nbsp;
Thursday 11>.&nbsp;To the north Sunny at times veiled; residual rains until morning in Piedmont.&nbsp; In the irregularly cloudy center; not excluded short showers on the coastal Lazio.&nbsp; To the south some rain in Campania. Friday 12 to the north: sunny and warmer. In the center: sunny and warmer; veiled in Sardinia. South: veiled but warmer. Trend: high pressure reassembly, new hot wave even more powerful than that of weekend 6-7 April. Sun prevailing until Sunday.&nbsp;

